From 123c948942e08bebca338e1b7dd481f43bca9fa2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 14:06:23 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 037/174] PGCL: mips initrd alignment and memory boundary fixes
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two fixes in arch/mips/kernel/setup.c for PGCL:

1. initrd_start alignment check: PAGE_MASK → MMUPAGE_MASK
   QEMU firmware aligns initrd to hardware page size (4KB), not
   kernel page size. With PGCL PAGE_SIZE=64KB, the PAGE_MASK check
   wrongly rejects properly-aligned initrds.

2. initrd end-of-memory check: PFN_PHYS(max_low_pfn) → memblock_end_of_DRAM()
   With PGCL, max_low_pfn is in 64KB kernel pages, so PFN_PHYS
   truncates to 64KB boundaries. MIPS reserves 256KB at the top of
   RAM, and QEMU places the initrd in the gap between the last kernel
   page boundary and the actual memory end. Using memblock_end_of_DRAM()
   checks against the real physical memory extent.

MIPS64 (Malta) boots to userspace with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4. TLB refill
uasm field overflow warnings are non-fatal (truncated andi immediates
work because high bits are already zero for valid addresses).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/mips/kernel/setup.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/kernel/setup.c b/arch/mips/kernel/setup.c
index 1ae6d0c0e1d6..b9cbc0ed0267 100644
--- a/arch/mips/kernel/setup.c
+++ b/arch/mips/kernel/setup.c
@@ -154,7 +154,7 @@ static unsigned long __init init_initrd(void)
 	if (!initrd_start || initrd_end <= initrd_start)
 		goto disable;
 
-	if (initrd_start & ~PAGE_MASK) {
+	if (initrd_start & ~MMUPAGE_MASK) {
 		pr_err("initrd start must be page aligned\n");
 		goto disable;
 	}
@@ -220,7 +220,7 @@ static void __init finalize_initrd(void)
 		printk(KERN_INFO "Initrd not found or empty");
 		goto disable;
 	}
-	if (__pa(initrd_end) > PFN_PHYS(max_low_pfn)) {
+	if (__pa(initrd_end) > memblock_end_of_DRAM()) {
 		printk(KERN_ERR "Initrd extends beyond end of memory");
 		goto disable;
 	}
-- 
